# Skill: Create Component

## Input

- `name` – component name in PascalCase (e.g. Macros, Button, NutritionCard)

---

## Instructions

When asked to create a component with a given `name`:

1. Create a folder:

`src/components/{name}/`

2. Inside the folder create:

componentName file `name.tsx `

1. Generate `name.tsx` with this structure:

- Import local CSS using:

```tsx
import './index.css';
```

4. Generate file structure.

```tsx
import "./index.css";

type {name}Props = {
  className?: string;
};

export const {name} = ({
  className = "",
}: {name}Props) => {
  return (
    <div className={`{kebab-name} ${className}`}>
      <div className="{kebab-name}__content">
        {name} component
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

```

5.  Generate empty index.css with base selector:
    `.{kebab-name} {}`

    No default export.
    No interface (only type).
    No inline styles.
    No CSS modules.
    No styled-components.
    No extra files.
    Always use 2-space indentation.
